Have you been here ? 

I did have a serene experience of attending the Ganga Aarti at Parmarth Niketan in Rishikesh. Watching H.H. Swami Chidanand Saraswatiji perform the Aarti himself was truly moving—it’s like being transported into pure bliss 

The calm and energy along the Ganga’s shores are unforgettable.🔆🔆

If you plan to go, park at one end of Janaki Bridge (only accessible by two-wheelers), cross, and then follow the path to the ashram. 
Aarti begins at 6 PM, but I’d recommend getting there by 5:30 PM to find the best spot by the river. 

As a special touch, the pandits offer Aarti thalis to everyone, making the experience even more beautiful.

#yogaretreat #rishikesh #gangaarti #parmarthniketanashram_rishikesh #parmarthniketan #divineexperience #thingstodoinrishikesh

From Ganga Arti to Yoga, we soaked up every moment in Rishikesh. 🌴☀️🙏🏻

⤵️ Here’s everything we did in Rishikesh for 24hrs. 

Our day at @alohaontheganges was nothing short of perfect:
	•	Arrived and got a warm welcome at 11am.
	•	Explored the beautiful property tour.
	•	Dived into an amazing lunch at 2pm.
	•	Took a swim with a stunning view at 4pm.
	•	Witnessed the spiritual Ganga Aarti at Parmarth Niketan at 5:30pm. 🕉️✨
	•	Played games at the clubhouse and relaxed.
	•	Had dinner at 9pm, followed by a peaceful walk near Laxman Jhula. 🌉

Next morning:
	•	Started with yoga at 7am.
	•	Visited Nim Beach at 8am for some quiet time.
	•	Wrapped up with breakfast at 9am before heading out.
